commentPostTextItems.html: Will Young has been adjudged the player of the match for his scintillating  innings. That is it from here, join us on Saturday for the second game.

What a stunning innings this has been from Will Young, stood there till the end and saw his team home. Chasing 203, New Zealand lost Martin Guptill just for 2 runs and then Nicholls and Young stitched 164 run stand and made sure there are no more hiccups. Rippon was the star of the match with both bat and the ball, scored 67 which helped the Netherlands to reach 200 mark after the early collapse and grabbed two important wickets
